{"name":"Dread Sorcery","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>You can wield the Art, the ability to bend the universe with your will. When you wield your implement, speak words of power, and lie to the universe, choose one of the following effects and <strong>roll +mind</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 10+</strong>, the effect takes place fully and as you intend it, your will is made manifest.</p>\n<p>&ndash;<em>Pyromancy</em> - Deal 3 area damage to a target within close or far range. You choose the form of your pyromancy, whether it&rsquo;s paper charms, writhing bolts of fire, floating blades, or lightning. It&rsquo;s more intense than any Art you cast with your implement and doesn&rsquo;t require reagents.</p>\n<p>&ndash;<em>Bind Shade</em> - You pull a shade (a deceased soul) or creature from the void into contact with you, enough to speak with it. It could be a specific person, or generic. It is bound to answer one question truthfully, then the connection dissipates if it so wishes.</p>\n<p>&ndash;<em>Red Word</em> - You curse a target that you can see, dooming it. At any point, by merely willing it, you can consume this curse to deal 2 damage to this target, not preventable or reducible in any way. This curse ends only when the target dies, you rest, or you willfully remove it. You may curse a target any number of times, and they are aware of its nature.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On a 7-9</strong>, your Art is successful, but choose 1:</p>\n<p>&ndash;You are fully exposed to harm, danger, or retribution</p>\n<p>&ndash;You can&rsquo;t speak that particular Art again until you rest</p>\n<p>&ndash;Take -1 ongoing to use your Dread Sorcery until you rest</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On a miss</strong> , your art writhes catastrophically. It fails, and in addition to other consequences, choose 1: You take 1 @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.ZT2tI7DJLtMzgm8B]{AP}&nbsp;damage from the backlash, or deal 1 @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.ZT2tI7DJLtMzgm8B]{AP} damage to an ally in range from the backlash</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"Mind","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/spells/horror-red-1.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"Bn2fAnNxSCFZRkJw"}
{"name":"Geomancy","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you have time (a respite or rest) and materials (alchemical substances, tallow, animal parts, charms), you can perform a dark ritual. Describe what kind of ritual you are performing to the GM. You could do any sort of ritual within the realm of reason - from summoning a dark creature, to resurrecting the dead, to spying remotely, to changing the weather (it still has to be ritual-like in nature).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It&rsquo;ll always work, but the GM will tell you one to four of the following you need to do to get it accomplished.</p>\n<p>&ndash;You and your group will risk danger from &lt;blank&gt;.</p>\n<p>&ndash;It&rsquo;s going to take significant time (hours, days, weeks)</p>\n<p>&ndash;It&rsquo;s going to cost more in materials and money than expected</p>\n<p>&ndash;You&rsquo;ll need to &lt;blank&gt; first.</p>\n<p>&ndash;You&rsquo;ll have to give up &lt;blank&gt; to do it.</p>\n<p>&ndash;You need help from &lt;blank&gt;.</p>\n<p>&ndash;You can&rsquo;t fully accomplish it - only a lesser, more unreliable version</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/spells/runes-magenta-3.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"HUfYns9kl5fcC6zO"}
{"name":"Mantra of Kaon, the Greedy","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you spend a power die to @Compendium[brokenworlds.basic-moves.8MTxd43hQwBbJsXr]{Channel Flame}, you can choose to roll a d6.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 5+</strong>, take the die as a new power die.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 1-4</strong>, give it to the GM as a break die.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/items/inventory/badge-coin.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"nLzBuyHZhPwefhML"}
{"name":"Pact","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Your power and prestige comes from a pact or agreement with a patron. Choose 1 and detail: (A devil, a master, a powerful ruler). While your patron is happy with your exploits, you can comfortably ask them for a favor at the beginning of each session, which they will always grant you. If they are unhappy or not confident in your exploits, they&rsquo;ll ask you instead. If you don&rsquo;t fulfill this request in due time, lose your ability to ask favors of your patron until you find a new patron, and you incur the wrath of your old one.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/skills/bat.png","effects":[],"_id":"f8i6dY2I0gcMdRrT"}
{"name":"A House Removed","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>You cut a small part of the Wheel (the universe) off for yourself. Your House is a medium sized structure floating in an empty void. Detail it to your GM. While inside you can&rsquo;t use your Dread Sorcery, but you can shape ambient features of the House by willing them into existence. Any modifications to your House can be made by you only and remain even if you leave it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To open a door to your House, you need time and safety, a door, a door frame, or portal-like structure (existing or self-constructed), and a key, which you forge (3 wealth, rare and dangerous materials). You can re-use the key and the door frame, and open a door to the house from any door in the universe, as long as you have the key.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Only targets that have the key or your permission can open a door to the House. Once inside, you can close and seal the door at your option. You can only leave your House from the same door you entered it through. However, you can also name a location which you have visited (for example, the glassblower&rsquo;s guild) and you can open a door from the House to another (real) door somewhere in the rough vicinity of that location. How precise it is and where you open that door is up to the GM.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Once you personally leave the House for a minute, the entrance disappears, trapping anyone left there within. You can only access your House twice between rests.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/skills/vortex.png","effects":[],"_id":"Zvorezoc1P5BJs9q"}
{"name":"Bloody Word","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you use your Red Word successfully on a target, you can gain the @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.tqNJrEQyIn6usOhG]{Stunned}&nbsp;tag to cripple it with fear or disorient it with pain, and cause it to also gain the @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.tqNJrEQyIn6usOhG]{Stunned}&nbsp;tag as long as you yourself have this tag. It is struck with terrifying visions of its own demise. These @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.tqNJrEQyIn6usOhG]{Stunned}&nbsp;tags end when you or your target take damage, or someone takes action to assist you or your target as normal.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"Kaon's Bloody Word","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/items/inventory/rune-red.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"ooi2xuiAzw5qVxbo"}
{"name":"Cut the Universe","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you want to cut a fiery path of nothing and transport you and your group across the universe instantly, name a location and <strong>roll +mind</strong>. If you haven&rsquo;t seen the location you wish to cut to, make a clumsy roll.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 10+</strong>, you come out where you intended, or somewhere close by.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 7-9</strong>, you come out roughly where you intended, but in somewhere very inconvenient (in the middle of enemies, far from where you need to be).</p>\n<p>On a miss, there is a mishap - the GM decides where everyone ends up (and how unscathed they are).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This Art, often called Division, is extremely rare and coveted by the rulers of the universe. Tell your GM how you came across it.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"Mind","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/spells/lightning-magenta-1.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"aIuovhIIqBHTZNT2"}
{"name":"Devouring Flame","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you fell at least one enemy with your pyromancy, you can draw on their dissipating soul flame to gain 2 stamina or heal 1 wound. This stamina cannot put you above your maximum.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/skills/shadow_06.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"MRdot6tN67hKdLyZ"}
{"name":"Erudite","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Choose two areas of study, as if they were a title of a book. (Example: Angels and the Pact, Daemonica Maleficum: The Orders and Features of Daemons). You are a master of these subjects as long as you study them, and can charge 2 wealth per rest for your services in tutoring and advice, as long as there&rsquo;s work in the area.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In addition, when you roll a <strong>10+</strong> on @Compendium[brokenworlds.special-moves.8HbnxYkZYWh1yfyy]{Query the Cosmos} about these areas of study, you make a breakthrough in your field, and you can tell the GM a new piece of useful information, hitherto undiscovered, about your subject area. The GM must accept this new information as fact, but can add to it in any way they wish.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can change subjects that you are studying when you rest, but may only have two at a time that you can devote your full attention to and gain the benefits of this move.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/items/equipment/books/book2.png","effects":[],"_id":"OR5LiUUyfujTtozg"}
{"name":"Kaon's Greedy Word","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you speak a Red Word, you can step on the target&rsquo;s shadow (if they have one). If you do, they are @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.aOBsubwgzIKSGYpR]{Crippled}&nbsp;in an area of your choosing. Additionally, they can&rsquo;t move from their spot until your foot is moved.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/spells/wind-grasp-eerie-1.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"V5FCK1I5rNJsDwqm"}
{"name":"Overcharge","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you roll a <strong>10+ </strong>on your Dread Sorcery, you can take an downside from the <strong>7-9</strong> list. If you do, your sorcery&rsquo;s targets are doubled.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/spells/beam-magenta-3.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"enpnZUfaD7dFGYQL"}
{"name":"Phoenix Blade","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>If you so choose, you can choose to have your Pyromancy deal 4 instead of 3 damage. However, you now suffer (or an ally suffers) 1 @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.ZT2tI7DJLtMzgm8B]{AP} backlash damage on a <strong>7-9</strong>, and 2 @Compendium[brokenworlds.tags.ZT2tI7DJLtMzgm8B]{AP} backlash damage On a miss.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/spells/enchant-red-3.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"cm16c2ySojYfd6rG"}
{"name":"Smother Flame","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you or an ally slay at least one enemy with @Compendium[brokenworlds.basic-moves.EHSRxOAZ0mcaeQuK]{Reach Heaven Through Violence}, or Dread Sorcery, you can instantly bind that enemy&rsquo;s soul as if you&rsquo;d just successfully cast Bind Shade.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"Strengthened Binding","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/skills/affliction_11.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"iYej07trY3WBxOXU"}
{"name":"Spin Wheel and Laugh at God","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you grasp the Flame Immortal with your terrible will, <strong>roll +mind</strong>. You may use this move a number of times equal to your +mind between rests.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 10+</strong>, you can completely erase the effects of something that just happened as if you had turned back time itself a few moments - damage, someone escaping your grasp, a mistake or misstep, even death. However, there are always minor unforeseen consequences - you turn things back slightly too far, or the result is slightly warped in some way.</p>\n<p><strong>On a 7-9</strong>, these consequences are major instead of minor.</p>\n<p><strong>On a miss</strong>, these consequences are even worse.</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/skills/emerald_01.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"Frp2tDmZbv228Upa"}
{"name":"Strengthened Binding","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you bind a shade, if there are materials (ash, clay, or dead flesh) nearby, you can additionally bind it into the shape of a steed or a servant (choose) after or before you ask it your question. The servant shade is bound to follow your commands unthinkingly. It can carry items and perform simple tasks, but cannot fight. The steed will never tire and can at your option fly or swim. It collapses and is destroyed when you rest. You can have any number of shades, but while you have a bound shade, take -1 ongoing to Dread Sorcery rolls</p>","class":"The Hunger","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/feats/command-undead.png","effects":[],"_id":"XVvFN6hdrictvkcg"}
{"name":"Sublime Binder","permission":{"default":0,"DFNIdbIQLd4K0XcA":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you bind a shade, you can bind it into a warrior form, as long as there are materials (clay, ash, dead flesh) nearby. Warrior shades are large, strong, and will perform simple, uncomplicated tasks for you on your command. As long as you have at least one warrior shade, deal +1 damage as your shades attack alongside you. However, each time you take damage while you have at least one shade, you lose one shade.</p>\n<p>Take -1 ongoing to Dread Sorcery rolls when you have at least one bound shade. You can have any number of shades, but if you miss a Dread Sorcery roll while you have any warrior shades, they break free and turn on you, dealing 1 ap damage to you or nearby allies per shade, then dissipate. They will collapse and are destroyed when you take a rest.</p>","class":"","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/brokenworlds/assets/icons/skills/violet_22.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"DKn33YvK1eiChkBR"}
